body:
Hi,

I'm getting a problem when running some code with hierarchical references, which results in an internal error:
```
$ verilator --cc failure.sv
%Error: Internal Error: failure.v:19:37: ../V3LinkDot.cpp:2304: Couldn't resolve inlined scope 'accessor_block' in: mod_a.u_a_mon.accessor_block
   19 |          bit read_x = mod_a.u_inner.x;
      |                                     ^
                        ... See the manual and https://verilator.org for more assistance.
```

```verilog
module mod_a;
   mod_inner u_inner;
   mod_a_mon u_a_mon;
endmodule : mod_a

module mod_inner;
   logic x;
endmodule : mod_inner

module mod_a_mon;
   function void accessor;
      begin : accessor_block
         bit read_x = mod_a.u_inner.x;
      end
   endfunction
endmodule
```

The above code was reduced from an internal design which is currently using verilator version 4.010 (and attempting to update to version 4.032). Git bisect suggests that the issue was introduced in #2176. 

Thanks,
James
